        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 24 at 5:02PM EDT until August 24 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>SVRBGM

The National Weather Service in Binghamton has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Madison County in central New York...
Southeastern Cayuga County in central New York...
Northern Cortland County in central New York...
Southeastern Onondaga County in central New York...

* Until 600 PM EDT.

* At 501 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Sempronius,
or 10 miles northwest of Cortland, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Homer, Cazenovia, Preble, Moravia, Scott, Truxton, Cuyler,
Georgetown, Sempronius, and Tully.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Heavy rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to flash
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
